{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01RthH7KyxfKAJZByJ439Kw7","type":"tool_result","content":"   820→  }\n   821→\n   822→  return results;\n   823→}\n   824→\n   825→/**\n   826→ * Apply dictionary-guided OCR repair to all words in a text string.\n   827→ */\n   828→function repairOcrText(text: string): string {\n   829→  return text\n   830→    .split(/\\s+/)\n   831→    .map((word) => {\n   832→      const match = word.match(/^([^a-zA-Z0-9À-ÿ]*)(.*?)([^a-zA-Z0-9À-ÿ]*)$/);\n   833→      if (!match) return word;\n   834→      const [, prefix, core, suffix] = match;\n   835→      if (!core) return word;\n   836→      const repaired = repairOcrWord(core);\n   837→      return prefix + repaired + suffix;\n   838→    })\n   839→    .join(\" \");\n   840→}\n   841→\n   842→/**\n   843→ * Apply blind OCR digit-for-letter repair without dictionary lookup.\n   844→ * Used to generate additional candidates for early-position lines where\n   845→ * positional evidence is strong enough to justify speculative repair.\n   846→ */\n   847→function applyBlindOcrRepair(text: string): string {\n   848→  if (isAllCaps(text)) {\n   849→    return text\n   850→      .replace(/1/g, \"I\")\n   851→      .replace(/0(?=[A-ZÀ-Ż])/g, \"O\")\n   852→      .replace(/(?<=[A-ZÀ-Ż])0/g, \"O\")\n   853→      .replace(/4(?=[A-ZÀ-Ż])/g, \"A\")\n   854→      .replace(/(?<=[A-ZÀ-Ż])4/g, \"A\")\n   855→      .replace(/5(?=[A-ZÀ-Ż])/g, \"S\")\n   856→      .replace(/(?<=[A-ZÀ-Ż])5/g, \"S\")\n   857→      .replace(/¡/g, \"I\")\n   858→      .replace(/€/g, \"E\")\n   859→      .replace(/[ÍÌ]/g, \"I\");\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"t